<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Chrome Extension</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/styles.css">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/chrome-extension.css">
    <link rel="icon" href="images/dbs-favicon.png" type="image/png">
</head>
<body>
    <%- include('partials/header', { mini: false }) %>
    <main>
        <section class="content-area">
            <div class="extension-hero">
                <h1>Baha'i Research Assistant</h1>
                <p class="hero-text">A powerful sidebar tool for researchers and editors to organize content across Baha'i websites.</p>
                <a href="#" class="cta-button">Add to Chrome</a>
            </div>

            <hr class="divider">

            <div class="feature-grid">
                <div class="feature-card">
                    <h2>Hierarchical Tagging</h2>
                    <p>Highlight text on supported Baha'i websites and apply custom labels. Organize your tags into a nested hierarchy of related concepts—similar to Evernote—allowing for deep, structured knowledge management.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="feature-card">
                    <h2>Crowdsourced Discovery</h2>
                    <p>Help researchers identify high-value items within large periodicals. Tag and classify distinct items, such as Tablets of 'Abdu'l-Baha in <em>Star of the West</em> or letters from Shoghi Effendi in <em>Bahai News</em>, making them easily retrievable for future study.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="feature-card">
                    <h2>Powering AI</h2>
                    <p>Your research contributes to the greater whole. The categorized items and hierarchy data generated by this tool directly power the hybrid RAG (Retrieval-Augmented Generation) engine behind <a href="https://bahai.chat">Bahai.chat</a>, improving answers for everyone.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>
    </main>
    <%- include('partials/footer') %>
</body>
</html>
